A. Overall Comments on Priorities
Since joining Capgemini in November 2024 as a fresher, I have consistently aligned my priorities with delivery excellence, continuous upskilling, and business value creation. I focused early on building a strong technical and professional foundation through multiple certifications and structured trainings across cloud, data, DevOps, and communication, which enabled me to become project‑ready quickly.
As I transitioned into client engagements, my priorities shifted toward billable contribution, quality delivery, and operational excellence. On the Hartford engagement, I moved from shadowing to independently handling migration execution, validation, production support, and special client requests. Based on my performance and delivery reliability, the client specifically requested creation of a billing position for me, which resulted in additional billability for the account, reflecting strong client trust.
In the current Cigna engagement, I continue to align my priorities with value‑added delivery, contributing to automation enhancements, script optimization, CI enablement, and complex issue resolution, while maintaining high compliance with utilization and delivery expectations.

B. Overall Comments on Skills Maturity
B1. What is the level of contribution this year?
My contribution has evolved from a fresher in training to a consistent, billable, and independently contributing team member. After completing foundational training and certifications, I applied my learnings effectively in live project environments.
On the Hartford project, I executed end‑to‑end GitHub migration activities across multiple waves, handled production defects, access and SSO issues, performed RCA for failed migrations, and supported critical delivery windows. My consistent performance led to formal client recognition and a dedicated billing role being created, directly contributing to project revenue.
In the Cigna project, I further expanded my contribution to automation development, migration tooling optimization, CI workflow enablement, and complex repo analysis, leveraging prior experience to deliver efficiently with minimal supervision.
Overall, my contribution has been high‑impact, quality‑driven, and business‑oriented.

B2. What level of leadership skills maturity is being demonstrated?
I have demonstrated strong early leadership maturity through ownership, accountability, and a solution‑oriented mindset. I take responsibility for complete outcomes, not just assigned tasks, ensuring quality, closure, and stakeholder confidence.
I proactively analyze issues, perform root cause analysis, and suggest automation or process improvements. I also actively support peers by sharing learnings and assisting in troubleshooting, which has been acknowledged through formal appreciation from leadership.
My ability to handle pressure situations, adapt quickly to new technologies, and communicate effectively with leads and stakeholders reflects readiness for higher responsibility and future leadership growth.

C. Overall Comments on In‑Year Contribution
During the year, I delivered strong in‑year impact by combining continuous learning with execution excellence. I completed multiple technical and domain certifications and consistently applied them to real client deliverables.
My contributions include:
- Execution of enterprise‑scale GitHub and GitLab migrations
- Independent handling of migration execution, RCA, and production support
- Development and enhancement of automation scripts, wrappers, and CI workflows
- Delivery quality that resulted in direct client recognition and increased billability
My work positively impacted delivery stability, turnaround time, automation efficiency, and client satisfaction. This year marks a strong progression from fresher onboarding to a confident, billable delivery professional, well‑positioned for promotion, higher responsibility, and continued growth.
